weekly_notes: Several teams left highly productive players on the bench across the week (examples: Trevor Lawrence 26.24; C.J. Stroud 28.76; Rico Dowdle 32.4; Justin Fields 25.92). Those bench decisions appear to have been consequential in multiple matchups.
There were both huge blowouts (SnydeRemarks 161.14) and extremely close games (Team Santangelo 125.44 vs Big Trouble 125.18).
Defenses and kickers swung margins in a few matchups (Saints D/ST +12.79 vs projection; Ka'imi Fairbairn 18.0; Eddy Pineiro 17.0).
Common pattern: single-player outperformance (WR/RB/QB) frequently determined outcomes when benches contained additional high scorers that were unused.
